<item>
            <title>[LU-9109] conf-sanity test_47: 0lustre-OST0000-osc-ffff8800788f4800 has lost lru_size: 100 vs. []&apos;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9109</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Bob Glossman &amp;lt;bob.glossman@intel.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/ea4efff2-eff6-11e6-8c0d-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/ea4efff2-eff6-11e6-8c0d-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_47 failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;0lustre-OST0000-osc-ffff8800788f4800 has lost lru_size: 100 vs. []
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;some instances of this failure have been filed as &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9059&quot; title=&quot;mount.lustre FATAL: unhandled/unloaded fs type 0 &amp;#39;ext3&amp;#39;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9059&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-9059&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  It&apos;s possible these all are really due to that problem but I&apos;m not sure.   From history this error only started recently, around 2/1/17.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;making a new ticket for this specific failure.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Info required for matching: conf-sanity 47&lt;/p&gt;</description>
